.TH IMGMOD-SOCSHARE 1 "July 7, 2026" "imgmod 1.0.0"
.SH NAME
imgmod-socshare \- Create a 1200x630 social sharing image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgmod socshare
[\fB-f\fR \fIFORMAT\fR] \fIINPUT\fR [\fIOUTPUT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B imgmod socshare
uses ImageMagick to auto-orient, center crop, resize, and extend an image to
1200x630 for Open Graph and Twitter card usage.

When \fIOUTPUT\fR is omitted, the output path is generated from \fIINPUT\fR as
\fISTEM\fB-pubshare.\fIFORMAT\fR. The default format is \fBjpg\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f \fIFORMAT\fR
Set output image format. Defaults to the output extension, or \fBjpg\fR when
output is omitted.
.TP
.B \-h
Show usage help.
.TP
.B \-v, --version
Show the plugin name and version.
.SH OUTPUT
The command prints the output file path and reports it through
\fBimgmod_output\fR so it can be optimized by \fBimgmod -o\fR.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B magick
ImageMagick command used to transform the image.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a JPEG next to the input:
.nf
.B imgmod socshare image.png
.fi
.TP
Create a PNG:
.nf
.B imgmod socshare -f png image.png
.fi
.TP
Write to an explicit WebP output:
.nf
.B imgmod socshare image.png share.webp
.fi
.TP
Create and optimize output:
.nf
.B imgmod -o socshare image.png
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imgmod (1)
